"{\"uid\": \"people.com-atlanta-olympics-bombing-richard-jewell-anniversary-8684601\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Two were killed and hundreds were injured after a bomb exploded in Atlanta's Centennial Olympic Park Dimitri Iundt/Corbis/VCG via Getty The2024 Summer Olympic Gamesare underway in Paris, as the world gets set to celebrate the greatest athletes in the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67, \"end\": 74, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5122332833645517e-17, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}, {\"begin\": 77, \"end\": 100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centennial_Olympic_Park_bombing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.93619680998825e-33, \"text\": \"Centennial Olympic Park\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centennial_Olympic_Park_bombing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centennial_Olympic_Park_bombing\"}, {\"begin\": 102, \"end\": 109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sly_Cooper\", \"score\": 0.9986114284052284, \"rank\": 0.0013905024070574217, \"text\": \"Dimitri\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sly_Cooper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sly_Cooper\"}, {\"begin\": 116, \"end\": 122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Branded_Entertainment_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Corbis\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Branded_Entertainment_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Branded_Entertainment_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vietnam_Coast_Guard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.878565316931522e-16, \"text\": \"VCG\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vietnam_Coast_Guard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vietnam_Coast_Guard\"}, {\"begin\": 182, \"end\": 187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999973156264, \"rank\": 2.684245324241966e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hundreds\", \"from\": 20, \"to\": 28}, {\"ngram\": \"a bomb\", \"from\": 48, \"to\": 54}, {\"ngram\": \"Getty The2024 Summer Olympic Gamesare\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 167}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 199}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest athletes\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But nearly 30 years ago, the world was stunned when a bomb killed two people and injured more than 100 others during the 1996 Summer Games in Atlanta.\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5122332833645517e-17, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"a bomb\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"two people\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 100 others\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 369}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1996 Summer Games\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The infamous bombing sparked a years-long hunt for the suspect, during which authorities falsely namedRichard Jewella suspect, before eventually clearing him of any wrongdoing.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 588, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The infamous bombing\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"a years-long hunt\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"the suspect\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"any wrongdoing\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 587}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The actual culprit would not be caught until years later.\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The actual culprit\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before Jewell was named a person of interest, however, he was heralded as a hero.\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"a hero\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell was working as a security guard at the '96 Olympics, when he noticed a green pack sitting under a bench in Centennial Olympic Park in Downtown Atlanta just before 1 a.m. on July 27,PEOPLE previously reported.\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centennial_Olympic_Park_bombing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.93619680998825e-33, \"text\": \"Centennial Olympic Park\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centennial_Olympic_Park_bombing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centennial_Olympic_Park_bombing\"}, {\"begin\": 871, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Downtown_Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Downtown Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Downtown_Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Downtown_Atlanta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"a security guard\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"the '96 Olympics\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"a green pack\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"a bench\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"1 a.m.\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 906}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After Jewell and a Georgia Bureau of Investigation agent unsuccessfully tried to locate the owner of the pack, the agent reported it as suspicious and a perimeter was created.\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"Investigation\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"the owner\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"the pack\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"the agent\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"a perimeter\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A minute later, a man called 911, saying a bomb had been placed in the park and warning, \\\"You have 30 minutes.\\\"\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"a bomb\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"the park\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"warning\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"30 minutes\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the homemade device was mistimed, and the bomb detonated at 1:20 a.m., only several minutes into the evacuation, before many people could leave.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the homemade device\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"the bomb\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"the evacuation\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two people were killed as a result of the blast.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Two people\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"the blast\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alice Hawthorne, 44, was in the park with her daughter at the time and was killed by shrapnel.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Septimus_Winner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice Hawthorne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Septimus_Winner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Septimus_Winner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the park\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"her daughter\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1501}, {\"ngram\": \"shrapnel\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her 14-year-old daughter, Fallon, survived.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1573, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her 14-year-old daughter\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"Fallon\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A 40-year-old Turkish cameraman and father of two named Melih Uzunyol died of a heart attack, which authorities said was \\\"precipitated\\\" by the bombing, as he rushed to take pictures of the scene, PEOPLE previously reported.\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_people\", \"score\": 0.7017272213380756, \"rank\": 0.42419895527654355, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"father\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"Melih Uzunyol\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"a heart attack\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"the bombing\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"pictures\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"PEOPLE\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1777}]}, {\"sentence\": \"111 others were injured, some of whom suffered head and chest injuries.\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"111 others\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1851}, {\"ngram\": \"chest injuries\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jewell was not seriously hurt.\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Soon after, Jewell was applauded for being the one who discovered the bomb and credited with helping save lives.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"the bomb\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"lives\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the attention would soon sour.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unbeknownst to Jewell, not even 24 hours after the bombing the chief of the Piedmont College Police Department, where the security guard had previously worked, had tipped off the FBI that Jewell had owned books about making bombs.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2129, \"end\": 2145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piedmont_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Piedmont College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piedmont_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piedmont_University\"}, {\"begin\": 2146, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Police_Department\", \"score\": 0.9999355826533808, \"rank\": 6.435619322840137e-05, \"text\": \"Police Department\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Police_Department\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Police_Department\"}, {\"begin\": 2232, \"end\": 2235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0804500953304531e-51, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Unbeknownst\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"the bombing\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2111}, {\"ngram\": \"the chief\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2121}, {\"ngram\": \"the security guard\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2189}, {\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2263}, {\"ngram\": \"bombs\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Authorities then began looking into Jewell.\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Authorities\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2295}, {\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 30, Jewell was interviewed byKatie Couricand he was still considered a hero.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2413, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2336}, {\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"byKatie Couricand\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"a hero\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2412}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But later that day, a report appeared in theAtlanta Journal-Constitutionthat changed everything.\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a report\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"theAtlanta Journal-Constitutionthat\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jim Gund/Sports Illustrated via Getty Jewell's name had been leaked to a reporter, who wrote that the FBI was investigating him and that he fit the profile they had developed of the bomber.\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.999996134645893, \"rank\": 3.865368517488357e-06, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0804500953304531e-51, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jim Gund\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"/Sports Illustrated\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2539}, {\"ngram\": \"a reporter\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the profile\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"the bomber\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2700}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though he was never arrested, Jewell became the subject of an intense media storm.\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2786, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"the subject\", \"from\": 2748, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"an intense media storm\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2785}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After nearly three months, Jewell was finally exonerated when federal authorities said he was no longer a person of interest.\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearly three months\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2812}, {\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"federal authorities\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2868}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2899}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Jewell filed several libel lawsuits, the FBI struggled to identify the actual suspect.\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 3006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2961, \"end\": 2964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0804500953304531e-51, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewell\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2926}, {\"ngram\": \"several libel lawsuits\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual suspect\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually, authorities zeroed in on Eric Rudolph, an anti-government terrorist, who placed three more bombs after the Olympic park one, injuring several others and killing a police officer, according to the FBI.\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Rudolph\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eric Rudolph\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Rudolph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Rudolph\"}, {\"begin\": 3216, \"end\": 3219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0804500953304531e-51, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"an anti-government terrorist\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3087}, {\"ngram\": \"three more bombs\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3116}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic park\", \"from\": 3123, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"several others\", \"from\": 3154, \"to\": 3168}, {\"ngram\": \"a police officer\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rudolph was placed on the FBI's Ten Most Wanted Fugitives List in 1998 and he would remain on the loose for five years.\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3222, \"end\": 3229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolph_the_Red-Nosed_Reindeer\", \"score\": 0.9663418776128285, \"rank\": 0.034829606883901056, \"text\": \"Rudolph\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolph_the_Red-Nosed_Reindeer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudolph_the_Red-Nosed_Reindeer\"}, {\"begin\": 3248, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0804500953304531e-51, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}, {\"begin\": 3254, \"end\": 3269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FBI_Ten_Most_Wanted_Fugitives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6374201432228316e-55, \"text\": \"Ten Most Wanted\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FBI_Ten_Most_Wanted_Fugitives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FBI_Ten_Most_Wanted_Fugitives\"}, {\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FBI_Ten_Most_Wanted_Fugitives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Most Wanted Fugitives\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FBI_Ten_Most_Wanted_Fugitives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FBI_Ten_Most_Wanted_Fugitives\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the loose\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3325}, {\"ngram\": \"five years\", \"from\": 3330